  "company": "Doordash",
  "industry": "Delivery and mobility",
  "year": 2025,
  "title": "Advancing Menu Content with AI: How DoorDash uses AI to generate menu descriptions",
  "ai_usage": {
    "description": "DoorDash has developed a production-grade AI system to generate high-quality, personalized menu item descriptions for restaurants. The system is built on a three-pillar architecture: intelligent retrieval, learning and generation, and evaluation and feedback. This AI system helps restaurants create compelling descriptions that reflect their unique voice and culinary style, improving online visibility and customer conversion.",
    "ai_components": [
      {
        "name": "Intelligent Retrieval System",
        "description": "A multimodal retrieval system that gathers relevant and accurate input data for menu items. It uses structured data extraction, vision model integration for photo-based ingredient extraction, and similarity-based retrieval to find descriptions from similar items within the same cuisine. This ensures the AI has a rich foundation of data to generate accurate descriptions."
      },
      {
        "name": "Learning and Generation System",
        "description": "A generation system that creates personalized, high-quality menu descriptions. It uses conditional prompting, in-context and few-shot learning, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), and real-time customization to adapt to each restaurant's unique voice and culinary identity. Merchants can choose from multiple tones (descriptive, concise, playful, enthusiastic) to match their brand identity."
      },
      {
        "name": "Evaluation and Feedback System",
        "description": "A hybrid evaluation system that combines automated quality control with human-in-the-loop review and A/B testing. Automated filters flag outputs that don't meet quality standards, while human reviewers provide nuanced feedback. A/B testing is used to validate business impact before scaling any model. The system creates a continuous feedback loop to refine prompts, retrain models, and improve quality over time."
      }
    ],
    "ai_impact": {
      "business_impact": "The AI system helps restaurants create compelling menu descriptions that improve online visibility and customer conversion. It addresses the challenge of generating personalized, high-quality descriptions at scale, especially for items with little or no existing data (cold-start problem). The system supports local businesses in presenting their offerings online, helping diners make more informed choices.",
      "technical_impact": "The system uses a combination of multimodal retrieval, retrieval-augmented generation, and real-time customization to generate high-quality, personalized descriptions. It also incorporates a robust feedback loop that combines automated evaluation with human insight to continuously improve the quality of AI-generated content."
    },
    "future_plans": "DoorDash plans to refine its models further to enhance the quality of each generated description. The company also aims to expand this technology to other areas, empowering merchants to showcase their offerings more effectively and elevate their presence on the platform."
  },
  "non_ai_components": {
    "description": "The system is supported by a cross-functional team of engineers, data scientists, and product managers. Human reviewers play a central role in validating content, tuning system behavior, and providing nuanced feedback that automation can't capture. The system also includes A/B testing to measure business impact before scaling any model.",
