{
  "title": "SQL Bot: A Conversational AI for Query Writing and Dataset Discovery",
  "introduction": "SQL Bot is a conversational AI tool integrated into DARWIN, designed to assist users in writing SQL queries, discovering datasets, and understanding query syntax. It has been developed over the past year by a virtual team with domain expertise in priority product areas. The tool has seen high adoption and positive user feedback, with ~95% of users rating its query accuracy as 'Passes' or above.",
  "key_features": [
    {
      "name": "Conversational Interface",
      "description": "SQL Bot provides a conversational interface that allows users to ask questions, receive SQL queries, and engage in follow-up conversations. It includes quick replies and guided experiences to help users refine their queries."
    },
    {
      "name": "Rich Display Elements",
      "description": "The tool incorporates rich display elements in the UI to help users understand recommended tables and queries. These elements include table descriptions, tags, access frequency, and links to DataHub for more information."
    },
    {
      "name": "Access Control Integration",
      "description": "SQL Bot checks if the user has the appropriate access to the datasets and automatically provides the code necessary to leverage the group's credentials. This reduces frustration for users, especially those new to SQL at LinkedIn."
    },
    {
      "name": "User Customization",
      "description": "Users can customize the experience by defining datasets for a product area, providing custom instructions, and creating example queries. These customizations are used when selecting tables and fields, and when writing and fixing queries."
    },
    {
      "name": "Ongoing Benchmarking",
      "description": "SQL Bot uses a benchmark set of over 130 questions to assess quality and performance. Evaluation metrics include table and field recall, hallucination rate, syntax correctness, and response latency. Human evaluation and LLM-as-a-judge are used to assess query accuracy."
    }
  ],
  "technical_details": {
    "architecture": "The modeling architecture of SQL Bot includes a user question classifier, a LLM re-ranker for table and field selection, an iterative query writing process, and a self-correction agent. The user's question is classified and delegated to the appropriate flow, with open-ended follow-up chats handled by an agent.",
    "query_writing_process": "The query writing process is iterative, with SQL Bot generating a plan and solving each step incrementally to build the final query. Solutions to previous tasks are stored in the chatbot's internal state to be provided to the next step. The query planner is instructed to minimize the number of steps it creates to condense queries for simple questions while maintaining performance on complex questions.",
    "validation_and_correction": "A set of validators is run on the output, followed by a self-correction agent to fix errors. Validators verify the existence of tables and fields and execute the EXPLAIN statement on the query to detect syntax and other errors. These errors are fed into the self-correction agent, which retrieves additional tables or fields if needed before updating the query."
  },
  "user_experience": {
    "integration": "SQL Bot is integrated directly into DARWIN, allowing users to access it within the same browser window as they write and execute their queries. This integration has increased adoption by 5-10x compared to a standalone chatbot application.",
    "intent_classification": "Intent classification is used to classify the user's question and decide how to respond. The tool can answer questions, find tables, provide reference queries, or ask general questions about query syntax.",
    "guided_experience": "Users have the option to enable a guided experience, where SQL Bot walks them through each step of the query writing process. This helps users understand the query and gives them more control over the query-writing process."
  },
  "customization_options": {
    "dataset_customization": "Users can define datasets for a product area by providing email group(s) or explicitly specifying the users and datasets to use. The product area's datasets are those commonly used by the group of users in that area, with the option to include or exclude additional datasets as specified.",
    "custom_instructions": "Users can provide custom textual instructions to SQL Bot directly in DARWIN. These instructions can enrich the overall domain knowledge of SQL Bot or provide guidelines for SQL Bot to behave in a specific manner to match user preferences.",
    "example_queries": "Users can create example queries to be indexed into the vector store. These can be added directly in DARWIN by creating a notebook and tagging it as 'certified.'"
  },
  "benchmarking": {
    "benchmark_set": "A benchmark set of over 130 questions was defined in collaboration with domain experts across 10 product areas. Each question includes a well-formulated question and ground truth answers.",
    "evaluation_metrics": "Evaluation metrics include table and field recall compared to the ground truth, table/field hallucination rate, syntax correctness, and response latency. Human evaluation and LLM-as-a-judge are used to assess query accuracy.",
    "results": "The use of re-rankers, descriptions, and example queries has increased table recall. Human evaluation and LLM-as-a-judge have been found to be effective in assessing query accuracy, with LLM-as-a-judge returning a score within 1 point of the human score 75% of the time."
  },
  "future_improvements": {
    "user_experience": "Future improvements include faster response time, in-line query revisions, exposing the context that SQL Bot used to answer the question, and learning from user interactions over time.",
    "semantic_accuracy": "Improving semantic accuracy could be facilitated by identifying champions to lead self-serve context curation efforts within their respective areas.",
    "high-roi_features": "The 'Fix with AI' feature has been identified as a high-ROI pain point, accounting for 80% of sessions and frequently saving users time in debugging their queries."
  },
  "conclusion": "SQL Bot has been successfully integrated into DARWIN and has seen sustained adoption. The tool has been developed by a virtual team with domain expertise in priority product areas. Future improvements will focus on enhancing user experience and semantic accuracy."
}

{
  "title": "Salesforce's Year-Long Journey with Agentforce: Lessons from the Agentic Enterprise",
  "author": "Joe Inzerillo, President, Enterprise and AI Technology",
  "organization": "Salesforce",
  "date": "2025-04-05",
  "summary": "This article details Salesforce's experience as 'Customer Zero' in deploying Agentforce, its autonomous AI agent platform. Over the past year, Salesforce has used Agentforce internally to transform customer support, sales, and employee services. The article outlines key lessons learned in agent testing, data governance, human-AI collaboration, and user experience design. These insights are now being used to refine the Agentforce product and help customers transition to an agentic enterprise model.",
  "key_points": [
    {
      "section": "The Counterintuitive Testing and Tuning Agents Need",
      "summary": "Agent success depends more on avoiding nuanced mistakes at scale than on comprehensive training. Early iterations of the SDR agent had a 30% 'I don't know' rate, which was reduced to under 10% through data cleanup and iterative training. The article emphasizes the importance of giving agents goals rather than prescriptive instructions ('letting the LLM be an LLM')."
    },
    {
      "section": "Data Fidelity is Tantamount",
      "summary": "Agentic AI requires consistent, high-quality data. Salesforce implemented a multilayered approach to data governance, source cleanup, and consolidation. The use of Salesforce Data Cloud helped unify over 650 data streams into a single source of truth, ensuring agents provide accurate and personalized support."
    },
    {
      "section": "Redefining Roles: The Human-AI Partnership",
      "summary": "Agents handle repetitive, tedious tasks, allowing humans to focus on complex, relationship-driven work. SDR agents are generating millions in pipeline from previously ignored leads, while customer service agents are freeing up teams to handle complex cases. This partnership model is redefining job roles and redeploying employees into growing areas like professional services and customer success."
    },
    {
      "section": "The Journey to Consumer-Grade Experience",
      "summary": "User experience is critical. Salesforce consolidated multiple agents into a single 'employee agent' and 'manager agent' to reduce fragmentation. Agents are integrated into Slack, CRM, web, and email, achieving 86% adoption in Slack alone and 99% global workforce adoption. The article stresses the importance of building agents into the flow of work."
    },
    {
      "section": "Closing Out the Year and Looking Forward",
      "summary": "As 'Customer Zero,' Salesforce is committed to experimenting, iterating, and refining the agentic enterprise model. The company is building its experience into Agentforce to deliver measurable ROI and simplify deployment. The article concludes with a commitment to guiding customers through this transformation with confidence and proven results."
    }
  ],
  "conclusion": "Salesforce's experience with Agentforce highlights the transformative potential of agentic AI in enterprise settings. By focusing on continuous iteration, data governance, human-AI collaboration, and user experience, Salesforce has laid the groundwork for a scalable, effective agentic enterprise model. These lessons are now being used to refine the Agentforce platform and help customers achieve similar results.",
